post_text:
Jets Girls Golf!
Great day on the course today as we defeated Flat Rock, 178-245. 178 is a new record score for the Jets in a match! Kristen Reed and Payton Bucki led the way with 42s, followed by Emilie Zlatos with a 46 and Ayessa Pidruzny with a 48. Everyone played great and we have moved to 2-1 in Huron League play.

When Wagar students were to come clean out their lockers and pick up their belongings, they were going to be greeted with a bright, cheerful scene! Thanks to a few community members for donating their Thrivent Financial Action Team funds, each student would see a pinwheel on their locker with positive attributes that teachers felt describes them.

However, we all know how things are constantly changing - so we had to roll with it. Since students are not able to enter the building, they will be getting their pinwheel with their locker belongings or when they turn in their technology.

We still wanted to share the beauty and cheeriness they provided!

post_text: "If you build it, they will come!" We received over 100 emails to foodsignup@airportschools.com We have added 2 buses, and adjusted other routes to accommodate more meal distribution. Day 1 = about 450 meals, Day 2 = about 970 meals...tomorrow we are going well over 1000 kids with meals in their hands! We do not have to repost the bus routes or new ones because we responded to every email that reached out to us. We will be pulling out of the Airport High School parking lot at 9:00 AM tomorrow for our deliveries. If you see a bus, flag us down! Remember kids, take a lunch, it helps us all and we love seeing you. If you email foodsignup@airportschools.com give us your name, address, and number of kids and we will respond and find you! text: "If you build it, they will come!" We received over 100 emails to foodsignup@airportschools.com We have added 2 buses, and adjusted other routes to accommodate more meal distribution. Day 1 = about 450 meals, Day 2 = about 970 meals...tomorrow we are going well over 1000 kids with meals in their hands! We do not have to repost the bus routes or new ones because we responded to every email that reached out to us. We will be pulling out of the Airport High School parking lot at 9:00 AM tomorrow for our deliveries. If you see a bus, flag us down! Remember kids, take a lunch, it helps us all and we love seeing you. If you email foodsignup@airportschools.com give us your name, address, and number of kids and we will respond and find you! Go Jets! Big shout out to the food service workers, bus drivers, and principals that are working hard to make this happen.

Airport Jets, I will continue to communicate through this FB page and my Twitter account. I will provide updates as often as necessary. This is what we are working on right now.
*We are developing a plan to provide learning and food throughout this extended closure. More details coming.
*Internet access is helpful, but we understand limitations. *Please see the generous move by Comcast below. IF YOU DO NOT HAVE INTERNET, APPLY FOR THIS PLEASE!

*You will not have random access to the school buildings during this closure.
*I will not be able to answer every question you post on this website, be confident we are probably working on it.
These are uncharted waters for all of us. I appreciate your support and patience. Understand we are all working hard for you and your students. We all need to pull together and get through this, and we will! Be safe and Go Jets!
John Krimmel, Supt.

post_text: Stop by Airport High School this evening for some fun activities! From 6:30 - 8:30 pm the 10th Grade English classes will present a Wax Museum. Students dress in character from their favorite book. We are also having "Jet Around the World" from 6:30 - 7:30 pm. Come join us in celebrating different cultures around the world. There will be games, dance performances, and snacks. Also planned is - Awareness Around the World at 6:30 pm. This interactive and fun event will teach you about individuals with different abilities, including: Autism Spectrum Disorder, Attention Deficit, Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD), Specific Learning Disability, Speech/Language Impairment, and many more. All activities are located at Airport High School. Hope to see you there!
